SIMPLE: skullcap
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skullcap
<hw>Skull"cap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A cap
which fits the head closely; also, formerly, a headpiece of iron sewed
inside of a cap for protection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any plant of the labiate genus
<gen>Scutellaria</gen>, the calyx of whose flower appears, when
inverted, like a helmet with the visor raised.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The Lophiomys.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mad-dog skullcap</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>an
American herb (<spn>Scetellaria lateriflora</spn>) formerly prescribed
as a cure for hydrophobia.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skullfish</ent>⟦br⟧
